@tnstateguard.org>
Cc: Keith Smith <keith.smith@tnstateguard.org>, Andrew Ammons <andrew.ammon=
s@tnstateguard.org>, Andrew Mule <andrew.mule@tnstateguard.org>

ALCON,
After several telecoms with S6/G6 personnel we have come to an understandin=
g concerning HF/WinLink comms during TNMAN26. Having worked with LT Mule, C=
W3 Roach and PFC Jernigan it is my intent to see the following steps be tak=
en:

  *   As is practical, all regiments, locations, and the JOC will participa=
te in HF Network communications per a published schedule during the week of=
 13 May - 17 May
  *   CW3 Roach will work with TEMA and TNANG to set frequencies and a sche=
dule of the HF Net. Net to include voice and digital traffic.
  *   CW3 Roach is to publish the comms plan and schedule requesting G6 for=
 review and approval
  *   Request that G6 disseminate the approved plan to all TNSG units after=
 final review
  *   Each Regimental S6 to respond to CW3 Roach and G6 their intent to par=
ticipate and personnel involvement
  *   Request that CW4 Simpson will oversee the use of P25 TACN radios at f=
ield locations he designates and provide training support as required
  *   MAJ Wemyss will publish AAR to LTC Estes and G6 upon exercise complet=
ion

2nd REG TOC

  *   51st SIG will set up and maintain a TOC at Falls Creek Falls on 12-13=
 May
  *   51st SIG will support HF, drone, and TACN missions communication requ=
irements as outlined above

V/r

MAJ David R. Wemyss
Tennessee State Guard
2nd Regiment - Nashville
=93Old Hickory=94
Commanding 51st Signal Battalion
